# Fix Container Launch Errors and Master Container Pathing

The issue is that when "Master Containers" are turned on, the container object instance is reused across different games. A container's [drives](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/container/Container.java#668-687) configuration stores mappings such as `A:/data/data/com.ludashi.benchmark/files/imagefs/home/xuser/Steam/steamapps/common/GameName`. For Master Containers, this is set once when the first game runs and is never updated for subsequent games, causing other games to fail launching because their Linux path is completely absent from the Wine environment, resulting in error `-1`.

## Proposed Changes

### [app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/utils/ContainerUtils.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/utils/ContainerUtils.kt)
We will add a new utility function `ensureGameDriveMounted` to dynamically check and inject the current game's path into the [Container](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/container/Container.java#25-1107) instance's drives string.
```kotlin
fun ensureGameDriveMounted(context: Context, container: Container, appId: String) {
    if (appId == container.id) return // Not a master container acting as proxy
    ...
    // dynamically inject the game directory into container.drives
}
```

### [app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/PluviaMain.kt](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/PluviaMain.kt)
In the [preLaunchApp](file:///home/max/Build/GameNative-Performance/GameNative-Performance/app/src/main/java/app/gamenative/ui/PluviaMain.kt#1046-1371) function, immediately after `val container = ContainerUtils.getOrCreateContainer(...)` (around line 1075), we will call `ContainerUtils.ensureGameDriveMounted(context, container, appId)` to ensure that the Master Container includes the [A:](file:///home/max/.gemini/antigravity/brain/8a00cef0-0df3-4c95-9a3b-9771c9a54394/task.md) drive map for the game we are currently trying to launch.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1. Enable "Master Containers" in GameNative settings.
2. Launch Game A (e.g. standard Steam game). It should launch successfully and populate [A:](file:///home/max/.gemini/antigravity/brain/8a00cef0-0df3-4c95-9a3b-9771c9a54394/task.md).
3. Launch Game B (a different Steam or GOG game). It should dynamically remount [A:](file:///home/max/.gemini/antigravity/brain/8a00cef0-0df3-4c95-9a3b-9771c9a54394/task.md) to Game B's path and launch successfully without throwing an error `-1`.
4. Disable "Master Containers" and ensure individual containers still work.
